<div id="content">                                       
                                            <p><a href="../index.html" >Club Penguin Help</a> &gt; <a href="../technical_help.html" >Technical Help</a> &gt; Remember me doesn&rsquo;t work</p>
                <h1>Remember me doesn&rsquo;t work? </h1>
              <p>This happens when your <strong><a href="glossary-technical-terms.htm#flash-player" >flash  player</a></strong> doesn&rsquo;t have enough room in it to save information from Club  Penguin. You can change your settings so that your flash player will have  enough room to remember your penguin from now on. Just follow these simple  steps.</p>
              <ul>
                <li><a href="#PC" >If you have a PC</a></li>
                <li><a href="#Mac" >If you have a Mac</a></li>
              </ul>
              
              
              <h2><a name="PC" id="PC"></a>If you have a PC:</h2>
              <div class="content-tall-left">
              	<ol>
			    	<li> 
			     	 Go  to the Club Penguin website. Click on &ldquo;Play Now!&rdquo; Then click on &ldquo;Start.&rdquo; You  are now on the Log In page.<br />
			      	<br />
			    	</li>
                	<li> Right-click  your mouse. A box will pop up. Click on the word &ldquo;Settings.&rdquo;<br />
                    <br />
                	</li>
			    	<li>                A  new box will pop up. On the bottom of this box you will see an icon that looks  like a file folder. Click on the file folder icon.<br />
			      	<br />
			    	</li>
			    	<li> You  will see a question: &ldquo;How much information can clubpenguin.com store on your  computer?&rdquo; Underneath the question, you will see a bar. Use your mouse to move  the arrow on the bar to the right. Move the bar until the number on the right  reads &ldquo;10 KB &rdquo; or more. That&rsquo;s about the same memory you need to view a  medium-sized thumbnail photo.<br />
			      	<br />
			    	</li>
			    	<li> Now  you should have enough storage for the computer to remember your penguin each  time you log in. Log in now, and click the box next to &ldquo;Remember Me.&rdquo;  The next time you log in, you will see a picture of your penguin on the screen  on the log in page.</li>
			  	</ol>
              </div>
              <div class="content-right">
              		<img src="images/Remember-meWin-step1.gif" width="350" height="220" /><br />
                    <img src="images/Remember-meWin-step2.gif" width="350" height="220" />
              </div>
              <div align="right">
              		<a href="#top" >back to top</a>
              </div>
			  
              
			  <h2><a name="Mac" id="Mac"></a>If you have a Mac:</h2>
              <div class="content-tall-left">
              		<ol>
                		<li>Go  to the Club Penguin website. Click on &ldquo;Play Now!&rdquo; Then click on &ldquo;Start.&rdquo; You  are now on the Log In page.<br />
                  		<br />
                		</li>
                		<li>Hold  down the &ldquo;control&rdquo; button on your keyboard and click the mouse at the same  time. A box will pop up. Click on the word &ldquo;Settings.&rdquo; <br />
                  		<br />
                		</li>
                		<li>A  new box will pop up. On the bottom of this box you will see an icon that looks  like a file folder. Click on the file folder icon.<br />
                  		<br />
                		</li>
                		<li>You  will see a question: &ldquo;How much information can clubpenguin.com store on your  computer?&rdquo; Underneath the question, you will see a bar. Use your mouse to move  the arrow on the bar to the right. Move the bar until the number on the right  of the bar reads &ldquo;10 KB&rdquo; or more. That&rsquo;s about the same amount of memory you  need to view a medium-sized thumbnail photo.<br />
                  		<br />
                		</li>
                		<li>Now  you should have enough storage for the computer to remember your penguin each  time you log in. Log in now, and click the box next to &ldquo;Remember Me.&rdquo;  The next time you log in, you will see a picture of your penguin on the screen  on the log in page.</li>
              		</ol>
              		
              </div>
              <div class="content-right">
              		<img src="images/Remember-meMac-step1.gif" width="350" height="220" /><br />
                    <img src="images/Remember-meMac-step2.gif" width="350" height="220" />
              </div>
              <div align="right">
              		<a href="#top" >back to top </a>
              </div>
              
            
</div>              
